A High Court sitting in Rivers State has restricted the People Democratic Party (PDP) from conducting the party’s South-South Zonal Congress in Port Harcourt The court granted the interim injunction restraining the Peoples Democratic Party, PDP, from going ahead with its South-South zonal congress slated for Port Harcourt today, March 9, 2021. The order was consequent upon a suit instituted against the party by four aggrieved members – Kingsley Ntuisong, Raphael Stephen Ntui, Ogar Solomon Aloho and Odama Thomas Odama. The applicants stressed that they were suing for themselves and also on behalf of some members who emerged PDP chapter chairmen in Ogoja, Calabar South, Akampa, Yakurr, Odukpani, Akpabuyo, Boki and Obubra local government areas of the state in the party’s Congress held on 21st March, 2021. Also joined in the suit is the PDP National Organizing Secretary, Col. Austin Akobundu (rtd). “1st Defendant ( PDP), her agents, privies or servants or howsoever called from holding its South-South zonal Congress on the 9th of March, 2021or any other date pending the determination of the Applicants’ Motion on Notice for Interlocutory injunction.” The court further granted the Applicants leave to serve the suit on the respondents by substituted means and adjourned the case to March 21st, 2021 for motion on notice.